Clone the python-app directory to follow along with this tutorial

Click the Docker Desktop icon to launch it, or use the following shell command:

open --background -a docker 

You will need to run the following commands to create a virtual environment to test the app:

python3 -m venv env
source env/bin/activate

Check the requirement.txt file to see the required packages
Run the following command to install the requrirements:

pip3 install -r requirements.txt

Run the following command to run the python application:

python3 app.py

Now we know for sure that app runs, we can build the container

docker init
